8. The length of this first intron is 223 base pairs.
9. There are 723 pseudogenes in the narwhal genome annotation.
10. In the human genome, the genes ZAR1L and N4BP2L1 flank the gene BRCA2.
11. In the Betta fish, the genes rnf32 and rbm33a flank the sonic hedgehog gene.
12. There is one copy of shh in betta fish.
13. There are two copies of shh in Atlantic salmon.
14. There are 26 genome assemblies available for Bos taurus on NCBI.
15. 11 of these available genomes are assembled into chromosomes.
16. Excluding sex chromosomes, Bos taurus has 58 chromosomes.
17. Chromosome 1 is the longest.
18. There are 1,033 annotated microRNAs.
